22const GenericGF &
23GenericGF::AztecData12()
24{
25 static GenericGF inst(0x1069, 4096, 1); // x^12 + x^6 + x^5 + x^3 + 1
26 return inst;
27}
28
29const GenericGF &
30GenericGF::AztecData10()
31{
32 static GenericGF inst(0x409, 1024, 1); // x^10 + x^3 + 1
33 return inst;
34}

37GenericGF::AztecData6()

41}

50const GenericGF &
51GenericGF::QRCodeField256()
52{

79/**
80* Create a representation of GF(size) using the given primitive polynomial.
81*
82* @param primitive irreducible polynomial whose coefficients are represented by
83* the bits of an int, where the least-significant bit represents the constant
84* coefficient
85* @param size the size of the field
86* @param b the factor b in the generator polynomial can be 0- or 1-based
87* (g(x) = (x+a^b)(x+a^(b+1))...(x+a^(b+2t-1))).
88* In most cases it should be 1, but for QR code it is 0.
89*/
90GenericGF::GenericGF(int primitive, int size, int b) :
91 _size(size),
92 _generatorBase(b)
93{
94 _expTable.resize(size, 0);
95 _logTable.resize(size, 0);
96 int x = 1;
97 for (int i = 0; i < size; ++i)
98 {
99 _expTable[i] = x;
100 x *= 2; // we're assuming the generator alpha is 2
101 if (x >= size) {
102 x ^= primitive;
103 x &= size - 1;
104 }
105 }
106 for (int i = 0; i < size - 1; ++i)
107 {
108 _logTable[_expTable[i]] = i;
109 }
110 // logTable[0] == 0 but this should never be used
111}
